  "body": "<!-- This form is for bug reports and feature requests ONLY! \r\n\r\nIf you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n> Uncomment only one, leave it on its own line: \r\n>\r\n> /kind bug\r\n/kind feature\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nUpon code inspection, found that kube-proxy server takes into consideration a bind\r\naddress of 0.0.0.0 (IPv4), but does not check for a bind address of :: (all-zeros IPv6)\r\nwhen calculating its node IP. \r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nIPv6 address \"::\" should be taken into consideration when calculating node IP.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nCode inspection.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): Latest master\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration**: VirtualBox cluster, Ubuntu 16.04.1 host, CentOS 7 guests\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): CentOS 7\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): 3.10.0-514.26.2.el7.x86_64 #1 SMP Tue Jul 4 15:04:05 UTC 2017 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n",
